    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like \"far outweighed\" is a pretty subjective way to put it. shouldn't we be looking at the actual data for things like the heavy metal mining and carbon footprint of manufacturing the blades/batteries instead of just comparing them to gas? isn't it possible that for certain regions or setups, gas might actually be less disruptive in the short term?",
